ngages most forcefully with autobiographical material, either in an effort to embrace it or denounce it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aAmerican poetryxHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aAmerican poetryy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aAutobiography in literature. 0aSelf in literaturexUSA. 0aSelf in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226103846423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226103846.jpg  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles